### 1. Firestore Triggers with Cloud Functions
You can use Firebase Cloud Functions to create a trigger that runs every time a new message is added to your database. Inside the trigger, you can send a notification to yourself using various methods, such as email, push notifications, or integration with messaging services like Slack.

